1
00:00:00,005 --> 00:01:00,005
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:01:27,029 --> 00:01:29,831
Someone's all happy, Hyun Jin.

3
00:01:36,788 --> 00:01:38,832
What?

4
00:01:38,832 --> 00:01:40,842
I don't have an umbrella...

5
00:01:51,303 --> 00:01:52,979
Yoon Seong?

6
00:02:00,145 --> 00:02:01,897
Where are you headed?

7
00:02:01,897 --> 00:02:03,857
Your umbrella's right here.

8
00:02:03,857 --> 00:02:05,992
What brings you here?

9
00:02:06,860 --> 00:02:08,946
There's something I need to say.

10
00:02:08,946 --> 00:02:10,663
Something you need to say?

11
00:02:12,032 --> 00:02:13,791
I like you.

12
00:02:16,620 --> 00:02:19,630
I really like you, Woo Hyun Jin.

13
00:02:20,874 --> 00:02:24,086
Ever since seven years ago, up to now,

14
00:02:24,086 --> 00:02:26,220
I still like you.

15
00:02:30,550 --> 00:02:33,060
I want to make things clear this time.

16
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:36,640
I'm done just watching

17
00:02:36,640 --> 00:02:38,566
from the sidelines.

18
00:02:42,938 --> 00:02:44,481
Yoon Seong.

19
00:02:44,481 --> 00:02:46,817
This is so sudden...

20
00:02:46,817 --> 00:02:48,701
It's not sudden.

21
00:02:49,403 --> 00:02:51,029
Saying these words

22
00:02:51,029 --> 00:02:53,080
took me seven whole years.

23
00:03:13,343 --> 00:03:14,761
Woo Joo.

24
00:03:14,761 --> 00:03:17,438
What did I tell you when Auntie shows up?

25
00:03:18,348 --> 00:03:21,108
Clap. That's right.

26
00:03:22,670 --> 00:03:25,423
Why isn't she here yet, though?

27
00:03:26,773 --> 00:03:29,534
Should we give her a ring?

28
00:03:37,159 --> 00:03:38,835
It's me.

29
00:03:42,414 --> 00:03:43,707
You'll be late?

30
00:03:43,707 --> 00:03:45,042
How come?

31
00:03:45,042 --> 00:03:48,336
Working overtime again tonight?

32
00:03:48,336 --> 00:03:51,055
No, that's not it.

33
00:03:52,132 --> 00:03:55,010
A dinner thing popped up last minute.

34
00:03:55,010 --> 00:03:57,637
I should've given you a heads-up.

35
00:03:57,637 --> 00:03:59,639
Dinner plans?

36
00:03:59,639 --> 00:04:02,100
You didn't say a word this morning...

37
00:04:02,100 --> 00:04:03,935
When this project is over,

38
00:04:03,935 --> 00:04:06,279
let's go on a date.

39
00:04:07,731 --> 00:04:09,066
Is...

40
00:04:09,066 --> 00:04:11,576
Manager Park with you right now?

41
00:04:18,700 --> 00:04:20,585
All right, I see.

42
00:04:24,956 --> 00:04:27,633
I got all excited for nothing.

43
00:04:29,544 --> 00:04:30,754
Auntie's going to be late.

44
00:04:30,754 --> 00:04:31,765
Should I take this off?

45
00:04:41,248 --> 00:04:43,874
[Episode 8]

46
00:04:47,312 --> 00:04:49,572
About what I said earlier,

47
00:04:50,982 --> 00:04:53,902
I don't expect an answer on the spot.

48
00:04:53,902 --> 00:04:57,280
I almost held out for a better moment,

49
00:04:57,280 --> 00:04:59,074
but you already know me.

50
00:04:59,074 --> 00:05:01,409
I used to just sit there overthinking

51
00:05:01,409 --> 00:05:03,961
without ever making a real move.

52
00:05:04,955 --> 00:05:07,874
The pitch schedule's still on our plate,

53
00:05:07,874 --> 00:05:09,960
and I won't pressure you at all,

54
00:05:09,960 --> 00:05:13,130
so sit with it and tell me when ready.

55
00:05:13,130 --> 00:05:15,757
I held this in for seven long years.

56
00:05:15,757 --> 00:05:18,142
A bit more waiting won't kill me.

57
00:05:24,099 --> 00:05:26,150
If you're torn about it,

58
00:05:27,310 --> 00:05:30,188
just try seeing me three times.

59
00:05:30,188 --> 00:05:33,567
Forget the senior or boss label,

60
00:05:33,567 --> 00:05:35,534
purely as a man.

61
00:05:36,361 --> 00:05:38,613
Since we crossed paths again,

62
00:05:38,613 --> 00:05:41,374
not once have we had any real quality time.

63
00:05:44,953 --> 00:05:46,830
That's true.

64
00:05:46,830 --> 00:05:48,498
Exactly.

65
00:05:48,498 --> 00:05:52,343
So at least let me have a shot
at winning you over, right?

66
00:05:56,172 --> 00:05:57,890
Let's eat.

67
00:06:13,273 --> 00:06:15,032
Thank you.

68
00:06:21,781 --> 00:06:23,541
Thank you.

69
00:06:24,159 --> 00:06:25,619
After the pitching's done this week,

70
00:06:25,619 --> 00:06:27,795
want to go on a date this weekend?

71
00:06:28,705 --> 00:06:30,464
What do you think?

72
00:06:36,171 --> 00:06:37,756
Sure.

73
00:06:37,756 --> 00:06:39,174
Then this time,

74
00:06:39,174 --> 00:06:42,093
I'll treat you to something really good.

75
00:06:42,093 --> 00:06:43,887
Sounds good.

76
00:06:43,887 --> 00:06:45,639
Go on inside.

77
00:06:45,639 --> 00:06:46,890
Okay.

78
00:06:46,890 --> 00:06:48,683
Drive safe.

79
00:06:48,683 --> 00:06:50,894
Oh, hang on, keep this.

80
00:06:50,894 --> 00:06:52,820
Rain's in the forecast again this week.

81
00:06:53,642 --> 00:06:54,648
No, really, I'm fine.

82
00:06:54,648 --> 00:06:56,233
There's one at my place already.

83
00:06:56,233 --> 00:06:57,692
This one's way bigger and works better

84
00:06:57,692 --> 00:06:59,277
for you and Woo Joo to share.

85
00:06:59,277 --> 00:07:00,995
Hurry up.

86
00:07:06,076 --> 00:07:07,494
I appreciate it.

87
00:07:07,494 --> 00:07:09,371
I'll head in now then.

88
00:07:09,371 --> 00:07:11,380
Get home in one piece.

89
00:07:35,146 --> 00:07:37,073
He crashed already.

90
00:07:52,247 --> 00:07:55,257
I really like you, Woo Hyun Jin.

91
00:08:15,520 --> 00:08:18,398
Manager, the field visit's today, right?

92
00:08:18,398 --> 00:08:20,650
Oh, the field visit.

93
00:08:20,650 --> 00:08:22,409
Let's go.

94
00:08:31,161 --> 00:08:33,379
I really like you, Woo Hyun Jin.

95
00:08:37,250 --> 00:08:38,251
Gosh.

96
00:08:38,251 --> 00:08:41,004
Thank goodness the client fixed it.

97
00:08:41,004 --> 00:08:43,264
We'd be pulling another late night.

98
00:08:46,092 --> 00:08:48,053
This is about a friend of mine, not me...

99
00:08:48,053 --> 00:08:49,304
Manager.

100
00:08:49,304 --> 00:08:50,847
You have friends?

101
00:08:50,847 --> 00:08:52,932
You think I don't have any friends?

102
00:08:52,932 --> 00:08:53,641
Actually, yeah.

103
00:08:53,641 --> 00:08:55,852
You're such a workaholic

104
00:08:55,852 --> 00:08:57,270
and so ridiculously put together,

105
00:08:57,270 --> 00:08:59,522
so obviously no one would expect
you to have any...

106
00:08:59,522 --> 00:09:01,149
friends?

107
00:09:01,149 --> 00:09:04,277
Anyway, my buddy, not me,

108
00:09:04,277 --> 00:09:05,612
is dealing with some kind of issue,

109
00:09:05,612 --> 00:09:08,122
and I'm clueless about this area.

110
00:09:08,740 --> 00:09:10,116
What kind of issue?

111
00:09:10,116 --> 00:09:11,826
Love troubles?

112
00:09:11,826 --> 00:09:14,204
That stuff is totally my thing.

113
00:09:14,204 --> 00:09:17,123
No, it's my buddy, not me.

114
00:09:17,123 --> 00:09:19,918
He told the girl he's into how he feels

115
00:09:19,918 --> 00:09:23,470
and she seems a bit uneasy about it.

116
00:09:25,256 --> 00:09:30,387
What kind of uneasy, though?

117
00:09:30,387 --> 00:09:33,473
Could be she flat-out
doesn't enjoy his company,

118
00:09:33,473 --> 00:09:34,432
or maybe

119
00:09:34,432 --> 00:09:37,435
it's nerves making her tense.

120
00:09:37,435 --> 00:09:40,480
If I had to pick, the second?

121
00:09:41,856 --> 00:09:44,317
Then that's hardly a red flag.

122
00:09:44,317 --> 00:09:46,403
She's probably just jittery
seeing him in a romantic light, no?

123
00:09:46,403 --> 00:09:47,737
Here's the catch, though.

124
00:09:47,737 --> 00:09:50,156
My buddy's kind of stung by it.

125
00:09:50,156 --> 00:09:52,575
She acts so casual with other dudes,

126
00:09:52,575 --> 00:09:54,512
but tenses right up around him.

127
00:09:56,538 --> 00:09:58,373
Couldn't that just mean

128
00:09:58,373 --> 00:10:00,841
she's trying to look her best?

129
00:10:01,835 --> 00:10:05,338
So it's positive then?

130
00:10:05,338 --> 00:10:06,339
Well,

131
00:10:06,339 --> 00:10:10,051
that's not necessarily a sure thing.

132
00:10:10,051 --> 00:10:11,719
Are you kidding me right now?

133
00:10:11,719 --> 00:10:14,188
You literally just called it a plus.

134
00:10:15,056 --> 00:10:16,558
Look,

135
00:10:16,558 --> 00:10:19,436
every person's wired differently.

136
00:10:19,436 --> 00:10:22,738
It varies by situation, you know?

137
00:10:24,023 --> 00:10:25,658
What?

138
00:10:26,260 --> 00:10:27,277
Please.

139
00:10:27,277 --> 00:10:28,319
Hey, see?

140
00:10:28,319 --> 00:10:29,237
What did I tell you?

141
00:10:29,237 --> 00:10:31,406
I told you he still has feelings for you.

142
00:10:31,406 --> 00:10:32,740
Hey.

143
00:10:32,740 --> 00:10:35,052
You seriously struck...

144
00:10:35,785 --> 00:10:37,203
Gold. Total gold.

145
00:10:37,203 --> 00:10:39,414
Were you even listening to me?

146
00:10:39,414 --> 00:10:40,832
I was.

147
00:10:40,832 --> 00:10:42,417
Two guys poured their hearts out to you

148
00:10:42,417 --> 00:10:44,210
at the exact same time.

149
00:10:44,210 --> 00:10:47,964
You know that legendary peak
everyone supposedly hits once in life?

150
00:10:47,964 --> 00:10:49,966
This could be yours right now.

151
00:10:49,966 --> 00:10:52,177
Soak it in.

152
00:10:52,177 --> 00:10:54,554
He offered three dates, no strings.

153
00:10:54,554 --> 00:10:56,681
Nobody's rushing your decision here.

154
00:10:56,681 --> 00:11:01,227
Meet both and figure it out later, huh?

155
00:11:01,227 --> 00:11:03,396
Soak it in, my foot.

156
00:11:03,396 --> 00:11:04,814
Looking Yoon Seong in the eye earlier,

157
00:11:04,814 --> 00:11:06,268
I felt weirdly uncomfortable inside.

158
00:11:07,529 --> 00:11:10,487
You were never the type
to be fully at ease with him anyway.

159
00:11:10,487 --> 00:11:12,155
- Me?
- Right.

160
00:11:12,155 --> 00:11:13,865
With your in-law, you let every single

161
00:11:13,865 --> 00:11:15,408
emotion out, raw and unfiltered,

162
00:11:15,408 --> 00:11:17,994
yet with Yoon Seong, the tiniest detail

163
00:11:17,994 --> 00:11:19,162
had you holding back.

164
00:11:19,162 --> 00:11:22,165
You can't measure him
against my in-law, though.

165
00:11:22,165 --> 00:11:23,416
Why is that off-limits?

166
00:11:23,416 --> 00:11:27,086
With my in-law, life just sort of

167
00:11:27,086 --> 00:11:30,590
threw us together, and we ended up seeing
each other at our worst.

168
00:11:30,590 --> 00:11:33,092
Maybe that's why he brings out

169
00:11:33,092 --> 00:11:35,978
the most honest version of me.

170
00:11:36,846 --> 00:11:40,649
But Yoon Seong doesn't do that for you?

171
00:11:42,227 --> 00:11:44,028
He's just...

172
00:11:45,230 --> 00:11:47,357
flawless in every possible way.

173
00:11:47,357 --> 00:11:51,152
So much to pick up from him, zero weak spots.

174
00:11:51,152 --> 00:11:52,612
Being near him makes me crave

175
00:11:52,612 --> 00:11:54,697
to become a better version of myself.

176
00:11:54,697 --> 00:11:57,082
I keep pushing harder because of him.

177
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:03,414
Forget it.

178
00:12:03,414 --> 00:12:06,235
My own heart's a mystery to me.

179
00:12:06,235 --> 00:12:09,112
Racking your brain won't crack this.

180
00:12:09,112 --> 00:12:10,880
Just wait it out.

181
00:12:10,880 --> 00:12:12,382
Sometimes the important answers

182
00:12:12,382 --> 00:12:15,267
come from your heart before your head.

183
00:12:18,372 --> 00:12:19,556
Hey, what was that?

184
00:12:19,556 --> 00:12:20,265
What do you mean?

185
00:12:20,265 --> 00:12:21,724
Didn't I just sound really mature?

186
00:12:21,724 --> 00:12:23,851
Right?

187
00:12:23,851 --> 00:12:24,894
Seriously...

188
00:12:24,894 --> 00:12:25,687
Unbelievable.

189
00:12:25,687 --> 00:12:27,605
Did that really just come out of my mouth?

190
00:12:27,605 --> 00:12:30,366
You're the reason I'm cracking up.

191
00:12:31,192 --> 00:12:32,402
You're back.

192
00:12:34,070 --> 00:12:37,122
Woo Joo, did you have a good time?

193
00:12:40,034 --> 00:12:41,953
Hey.

194
00:12:41,953 --> 00:12:44,731
You shared a bed with Woo Joo.

195
00:12:44,731 --> 00:12:45,790
Wasn't that a tight squeeze?

196
00:12:45,790 --> 00:12:48,258
I just fell asleep
because you were taking a while.

197
00:12:49,586 --> 00:12:53,472
Yesterday must've been a real blast.

198
00:12:54,966 --> 00:12:57,017
No, not really...

199
00:13:00,930 --> 00:13:02,599
Were you up

200
00:13:02,599 --> 00:13:04,691
waiting for me?

201
00:13:06,102 --> 00:13:08,370
We never set anything up, so why?

202
00:13:10,048 --> 00:13:12,050
What's with ramen? Have real food.

203
00:13:12,050 --> 00:13:14,660
Should I pull out some kimchi?

204
00:13:17,530 --> 00:13:18,656
Wait, cake?

205
00:13:18,656 --> 00:13:19,949
Who's this for?

206
00:13:19,949 --> 00:13:21,451
That's for you.

207
00:13:21,451 --> 00:13:22,619
For me?

208
00:13:22,619 --> 00:13:25,379
Why? My birthday isn't today.

209
00:13:26,539 --> 00:13:29,000
I heard that pitch was really major.

210
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:31,127
You went through so much trouble
preparing for that.

211
00:13:31,127 --> 00:13:34,513
Pulling all-nighters, skipping meals.

212
00:13:35,423 --> 00:13:37,216
Word is you nailed it,

213
00:13:37,216 --> 00:13:40,094
so I figured a small party was in order.

214
00:13:40,094 --> 00:13:42,639
Hold on, this was a surprise?

215
00:13:42,639 --> 00:13:44,307
Why didn't you say something earlier?

216
00:13:44,307 --> 00:13:46,316
I'd have rushed right back.

217
00:13:48,186 --> 00:13:50,355
Wait, chocolate cake!

218
00:13:50,355 --> 00:13:52,614
Chocolate cake's my favorite.

219
00:13:53,316 --> 00:13:54,877
You like chocolate cake?

220
00:13:58,237 --> 00:14:00,414
This looks so good.

221
00:14:01,824 --> 00:14:03,459
Thanks.

222
00:14:08,414 --> 00:14:10,625
It's delicious.

223
00:14:10,625 --> 00:14:12,801
A bit overdue, but congrats.

224
00:14:13,836 --> 00:14:16,388
All that effort for the pitch paid off.

225
00:14:17,674 --> 00:14:19,092
Thank you.

226
00:14:19,092 --> 00:14:21,310
For real, so much credit goes to you.

227
00:14:21,928 --> 00:14:24,730
Please, I barely lifted a finger.

228
00:14:29,102 --> 00:14:31,062
It's rich and tasty.

229
00:14:31,062 --> 00:14:33,030
Did this come from a popular shop?

230
00:14:42,740 --> 00:14:44,541
Hey.

231
00:14:49,580 --> 00:14:51,735
Mind if I try a little?

232
00:14:51,735 --> 00:14:53,188
Hold on, you told me you had dinner.

233
00:14:54,168 --> 00:14:57,004
But after all that sugar,
I need a kick of heat.

234
00:14:57,004 --> 00:14:58,798
Want me to make you some ramen?

235
00:14:58,798 --> 00:15:01,099
Just one bite is all I need.

236
00:15:01,843 --> 00:15:04,011
Seriously, only a taste.

237
00:15:04,011 --> 00:15:06,472
I swear, just a nibble.

238
00:15:06,472 --> 00:15:08,398
Watch out, that's steaming.

239
00:15:13,423 --> 00:15:15,565
It's so good.

240
00:15:15,565 --> 00:15:17,233
Your ramen skills are no joke.

241
00:15:17,233 --> 00:15:19,109
Wait a sec.

242
00:15:19,989 --> 00:15:22,196
Hang on, stop right there.

243
00:15:22,196 --> 00:15:24,365
Tying your hair back? One bite!

244
00:15:24,365 --> 00:15:25,908
A single bite feels heartless.

245
00:15:25,908 --> 00:15:27,452
Let me sneak in one more.

246
00:15:27,452 --> 00:15:29,328
Oh, so two bites means generous now?

247
00:15:29,328 --> 00:15:30,913
Please, just one more.

248
00:15:30,913 --> 00:15:32,540
Okay, one bite. That's the limit.

249
00:15:32,540 --> 00:15:33,374
A single bite.

250
00:15:33,374 --> 00:15:34,876
Seriously, only one.

251
00:15:34,876 --> 00:15:38,053
Then let me take one about this size.

252
00:15:53,420 --> 00:15:55,179
[PM 5:00 Pick up Woo Joo]

253
00:16:02,945 --> 00:16:04,580
Who's...

254
00:16:05,740 --> 00:16:07,200
It's you.

255
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:08,159
Just getting home from the office?

256
00:16:08,159 --> 00:16:11,078
Since he kept an eye on Woo Joo,

257
00:16:11,078 --> 00:16:13,873
I told him let's have dinner together.

258
00:16:13,873 --> 00:16:16,049
Step inside for a minute.

259
00:16:19,670 --> 00:16:22,180
Get in here, hurry up.

260
00:16:26,260 --> 00:16:27,678
Did you grab a bite yet?

261
00:16:27,678 --> 00:16:30,723
I whipped up fresh greens. Try some first.

262
00:16:30,723 --> 00:16:33,609
I really appreciate it, but I'm full.

263
00:16:34,227 --> 00:16:37,070
- We'd better head out now.
- Sure.

264
00:16:41,275 --> 00:16:43,462
Is playing with me really that fun?

265
00:16:47,240 --> 00:16:48,825
Woo Joo, let's go.

266
00:16:48,825 --> 00:16:50,326
Come here.

267
00:16:50,326 --> 00:16:52,345
Bye.

268
00:16:53,287 --> 00:16:55,414
Here. Take this.

269
00:16:55,414 --> 00:16:59,293
I heard that a cold is spreading
at daycare lately.

270
00:16:59,293 --> 00:17:00,962
Apparently pear and bellflower juice

271
00:17:00,962 --> 00:17:02,755
does wonders for immunity,

272
00:17:02,755 --> 00:17:03,589
so feed this to Woo Joo.

273
00:17:03,589 --> 00:17:06,092
Goodness, shopping for his grandkid,

274
00:17:06,092 --> 00:17:09,637
he scrutinized every single thing.

275
00:17:09,637 --> 00:17:10,847
It's all made locally

276
00:17:10,847 --> 00:17:12,890
with homegrown ingredients,

277
00:17:12,890 --> 00:17:16,602
so bring it along and have him sip daily.

278
00:17:16,602 --> 00:17:18,779
Make sure he enjoys it.

279
00:17:28,531 --> 00:17:30,449
Is playing with me really that fun?

280
00:17:30,449 --> 00:17:31,701
Goodness, shopping for his grandkid,

281
00:17:31,701 --> 00:17:36,088
he scrutinized every single thing.

282
00:17:36,706 --> 00:17:39,375
Sun Woo Joo.

283
00:17:39,375 --> 00:17:41,812
You love your grandpa that much?

284
00:17:51,470 --> 00:17:53,188
Who is it?

285
00:18:05,255 --> 00:18:06,465
It's me.

286
00:18:06,465 --> 00:18:07,383
Where are you?

287
00:18:07,383 --> 00:18:08,258
Me?

288
00:18:08,258 --> 00:18:10,260
I'm almost there. Why?

289
00:18:10,260 --> 00:18:11,553
Well,

290
00:18:11,553 --> 00:18:13,430
the thing is...

291
00:18:13,430 --> 00:18:16,483
I think you're going to need to come over here.

292
00:18:18,560 --> 00:18:21,404
I made it. What's going on?

293
00:18:22,064 --> 00:18:23,357
Who is she?

294
00:18:23,357 --> 00:18:26,785
She said she's from the insurance agency.

295
00:18:31,657 --> 00:18:33,701
For the death benefit,

296
00:18:33,701 --> 00:18:36,954
you need to file your claim within three years

297
00:18:36,954 --> 00:18:39,790
so we can start the payout process.

298
00:18:39,790 --> 00:18:41,750
Of course, if you have questions

299
00:18:41,750 --> 00:18:43,335
about the payout process like today,

300
00:18:43,335 --> 00:18:46,130
we also offer
in-person consultations like this one.

301
00:18:46,130 --> 00:18:47,339
As you can see right here,

302
00:18:47,339 --> 00:18:49,591
there's a little over 100 million won ready

303
00:18:49,591 --> 00:18:51,301
to be paid out

304
00:18:51,301 --> 00:18:53,178
under both Woo Hyun Joo
and Sun Woo Jin's names.

305
00:18:53,178 --> 00:18:55,305
And if you look here,
this is the list of documents

306
00:18:55,305 --> 00:18:57,808
you're going to need to get the payout.

307
00:18:57,808 --> 00:19:01,069
Do you have any other questions for me?

308
00:19:02,104 --> 00:19:03,822
No.

309
00:19:21,253 --> 00:19:24,430
[Death Benefit Payout Process Guide]

310
00:19:34,808 --> 00:19:35,850
Hyun Jin.

311
00:19:35,850 --> 00:19:36,680
Oh, right.

312
00:19:36,680 --> 00:19:38,057
I should buy diapers for Woo Joo.
I completely forgot.

313
00:19:38,057 --> 00:19:39,016
Let me just run out and grab some real quick.

314
00:19:39,016 --> 00:19:40,225
Right now? Don't sweat it.

315
00:19:40,225 --> 00:19:41,935
I'm going to pick some up on my way home
from work tomorrow.

316
00:19:41,935 --> 00:19:44,521
No, the convenience store is
right around the corner anyway.

317
00:19:44,521 --> 00:19:46,364
I'll be right back.

318
00:20:24,228 --> 00:20:26,522
Where's Woo Joo?

319
00:20:26,522 --> 00:20:28,323
Next door.

320
00:20:31,819 --> 00:20:34,871
You said you were going to buy diapers,
but you left your wallet behind.

321
00:20:37,282 --> 00:20:40,911
I had a feeling this would happen,
so I came over.

322
00:20:40,911 --> 00:20:43,171
I didn't think you'd be handling it well.

323
00:20:47,543 --> 00:20:51,012
I honestly thought I was keeping it together.

324
00:20:54,174 --> 00:20:56,392
Turns out I wasn't.

325
00:21:07,771 --> 00:21:10,657
You can't just suppress something like that.

326
00:21:12,317 --> 00:21:14,069
It's just...

327
00:21:14,069 --> 00:21:17,330
Some days you feel like you're okay,

328
00:21:20,576 --> 00:21:23,252
then other days you miss them all over again.

329
00:21:23,996 --> 00:21:27,382
You just keep on living
while carrying that ache.

330
00:21:28,375 --> 00:21:30,176
So

331
00:21:31,128 --> 00:21:33,012
let it out.

332
00:21:34,548 --> 00:21:36,675
Bottling it up at a time like this

333
00:21:36,675 --> 00:21:38,685
only makes it worse.

334
00:21:43,932 --> 00:21:46,901
I really wanted to tough it out.

335
00:21:49,563 --> 00:21:52,448
And I really was.

336
00:21:57,909 --> 00:22:01,116
But a death benefit payout?

337
00:22:01,116 --> 00:22:04,127
That's just brutal.

338
00:22:04,828 --> 00:22:08,881
Hearing it put like that makes it sound so...

339
00:22:47,037 --> 00:22:48,956
What are you up to?

340
00:22:48,956 --> 00:22:51,416
Isn't the GloMarket meeting coming up?

341
00:22:51,416 --> 00:22:54,294
Yeah, I already got everything ready, but...

342
00:22:54,294 --> 00:22:57,005
Please tell me you're not still
agonizing over the kit lineup.

343
00:22:57,005 --> 00:22:59,007
Everyone signed off on it
at the executive meeting, didn't they?

344
00:22:59,007 --> 00:23:00,092
That's what I'm saying.

345
00:23:00,092 --> 00:23:01,885
Honestly, Hyun Jin,

346
00:23:01,885 --> 00:23:03,637
you're the kind of person
who creates problems for yourself.

347
00:23:03,637 --> 00:23:06,473
Think about how many people worked
on that single meal kit.

348
00:23:06,473 --> 00:23:09,233
What more can you possibly do at this point?

349
00:23:12,020 --> 00:23:14,197
Fair enough, but...

350
00:23:14,815 --> 00:23:17,526
That was Woo Hyun Jin's idea?

351
00:23:17,526 --> 00:23:20,570
How'd she even come up
with putting a tteokbokki bowl in there?

352
00:23:20,570 --> 00:23:23,323
So did GloMarket close the deal?

353
00:23:23,323 --> 00:23:25,993
Yes, we signed an exclusive contract with BS,

354
00:23:25,993 --> 00:23:27,828
and we're kicking off
with the tteokbokki meal kit

355
00:23:27,828 --> 00:23:29,705
before expanding into more items.

356
00:23:29,705 --> 00:23:30,914
Classic you.

357
00:23:30,914 --> 00:23:33,083
Pulled off another one.

358
00:23:33,083 --> 00:23:35,419
Speaking of which,
the contract-to-permanent employees,

359
00:23:35,419 --> 00:23:38,596
isn't it about time we lock in the final picks?

360
00:23:44,720 --> 00:23:47,472
When was the last time
I actually clocked out on time?

361
00:23:47,472 --> 00:23:48,557
Feel like grabbing a drink?

362
00:23:48,557 --> 00:23:49,599
Absolutely.

363
00:23:49,599 --> 00:23:51,275
Love it.

364
00:23:56,231 --> 00:23:58,491
Excuse me, sorry.

365
00:24:11,239 --> 00:24:13,552
What do you feel like doing tomorrow?

366
00:24:26,887 --> 00:24:28,813
Where are we headed right now?

367
00:24:30,390 --> 00:24:32,125
Who knows.

368
00:24:52,079 --> 00:24:53,997
This is gorgeous.

369
00:24:53,997 --> 00:24:55,874
I'm glad.

370
00:24:55,874 --> 00:24:58,710
You've been glued to your screen lately,

371
00:24:58,710 --> 00:25:00,962
so I figured you needed a breather.

372
00:25:00,962 --> 00:25:02,972
You've worked hard.

373
00:25:04,216 --> 00:25:05,884
I know you went to bat for me

374
00:25:05,884 --> 00:25:09,687
and gave me a real shot to prove myself.

375
00:25:10,430 --> 00:25:11,765
That means a lot, truly.

376
00:25:11,765 --> 00:25:14,518
For you,

377
00:25:14,518 --> 00:25:17,396
I'd make something out of nothing.

378
00:25:17,396 --> 00:25:19,648
I already put my heart out there anyway,

379
00:25:19,648 --> 00:25:21,741
might as well go all in.

380
00:25:24,027 --> 00:25:25,570
Let's go.

381
00:25:25,570 --> 00:25:27,788
We're already here, so let's enjoy it.

382
00:25:48,385 --> 00:25:50,294
Oh, you scared me.

383
00:25:50,294 --> 00:25:51,221
Hi.

384
00:25:51,221 --> 00:25:52,722
Hi.

385
00:25:52,722 --> 00:25:54,440
So cute.

386
00:26:06,695 --> 00:26:09,372
Yeah, I can read it fine, it's in huge letters.

387
00:26:12,242 --> 00:26:13,952
How did you pull all this together?

388
00:26:13,952 --> 00:26:16,371
I haven't made kimbap in forever,
so no promises on how it tastes.

389
00:26:16,371 --> 00:26:18,089
Go ahead, try some.

390
00:26:23,259 --> 00:26:24,296
This is delicious!

391
00:26:24,296 --> 00:26:26,264
You dig in too.

392
00:26:29,634 --> 00:26:32,345
I made it, but yeah, it is pretty good.

393
00:26:32,345 --> 00:26:33,388
Oh, right.

394
00:26:33,388 --> 00:26:35,515
There's something I've been curious about.

395
00:26:35,515 --> 00:26:38,018
Why did you choose BS?

396
00:26:38,018 --> 00:26:39,026
With your resume,

397
00:26:39,026 --> 00:26:41,988
you could've landed
somewhere way more prestigious.

398
00:26:43,106 --> 00:26:46,151
"Food is the button
that opens the door to memory."

399
00:26:46,151 --> 00:26:49,321
Wait, that was from my cover letter.

400
00:26:49,321 --> 00:26:51,823
That line really resonated with me too.

401
00:26:51,823 --> 00:26:55,202
I want the food people pick up on the cheap,
without thinking twice,

402
00:26:55,202 --> 00:26:57,204
to actually taste incredible,

403
00:26:57,204 --> 00:27:00,457
so the memories attached to it are happy ones.

404
00:27:00,457 --> 00:27:01,958
I don't want our products to be

405
00:27:01,958 --> 00:27:05,128
frozen meals people choke down
out of necessity.

406
00:27:05,128 --> 00:27:06,421
I want them to be so good

407
00:27:06,421 --> 00:27:10,550
that for just a moment,
everything else fades away.

408
00:27:10,550 --> 00:27:11,676
I feel the exact same way.

409
00:27:11,676 --> 00:27:15,013
That's the whole reason
I had my heart set on BS.

410
00:27:15,013 --> 00:27:16,890
My sister and I

411
00:27:16,890 --> 00:27:19,768
built so many memories
around frozen food growing up.

412
00:27:19,768 --> 00:27:21,353
Now every time I have kimbap,

413
00:27:21,353 --> 00:27:23,396
you're going to cross my mind.

414
00:27:23,396 --> 00:27:25,323
Including right now.

415
00:27:27,150 --> 00:27:29,569
You know,

416
00:27:29,569 --> 00:27:31,905
you're actually

417
00:27:31,905 --> 00:27:33,956
kind of cheesy, right?

418
00:27:35,867 --> 00:27:37,285
I'm just kidding.

419
00:27:37,285 --> 00:27:39,371
Let's just eat.

420
00:27:39,371 --> 00:27:42,381
I really love fruit too.

421
00:27:45,497 --> 00:27:46,503
What's wrong?

422
00:27:46,503 --> 00:27:48,797
What's all the commotion about this early?

423
00:27:48,797 --> 00:27:50,298
Hyun Jin,

424
00:27:50,298 --> 00:27:52,551
I never doubted you for a second.

425
00:27:52,551 --> 00:27:54,477
Seriously, I'm so proud.

426
00:27:55,345 --> 00:27:57,264
What are you talking about?

427
00:27:57,264 --> 00:27:58,640
Word is...

428
00:27:58,640 --> 00:28:00,850
you're getting converted to permanent.

429
00:28:00,850 --> 00:28:01,935
Are you serious right now?

430
00:28:01,935 --> 00:28:04,020
Dead serious.

431
00:28:04,020 --> 00:28:06,940
I literally just ran
into my HR connect on the way over.

432
00:28:06,940 --> 00:28:08,775
Out of everyone
in the contract-to-permanent pool,

433
00:28:08,775 --> 00:28:10,819
your scores blew everyone else
out of the water.

434
00:28:10,819 --> 00:28:13,863
You're the frontrunner for the permanent spot.

435
00:28:13,863 --> 00:28:16,040
No. You're basically a lock.

436
00:28:16,746 --> 00:28:18,243
Oh my gosh.

437
00:28:18,243 --> 00:28:19,953
I'm over the moon right now.

438
00:28:19,953 --> 00:28:22,376
This doesn't even feel real.

439
00:28:22,376 --> 00:28:23,771
You worked your tail off for this.

440
00:28:23,771 --> 00:28:26,167
Juggling work
and raising Woo Joo all by yourself,

441
00:28:26,167 --> 00:28:28,886
I can only imagine what that took out of you.

442
00:28:30,343 --> 00:28:31,423
Thank you.

443
00:28:31,423 --> 00:28:34,134
Congratulations, truly.

444
00:28:34,134 --> 00:28:36,386
Alright, please go
over the final package design

445
00:28:36,386 --> 00:28:38,096
from Filmpluto one more time,

446
00:28:38,096 --> 00:28:39,973
and for everyone else, hang in there

447
00:28:39,973 --> 00:28:41,683
until launch day.

448
00:28:41,683 --> 00:28:43,977
You all did amazing.

449
00:28:43,977 --> 00:28:45,020
- Good work.
- Great job, everyone.

450
00:28:45,020 --> 00:28:47,276
Good work, everyone.

451
00:28:47,276 --> 00:28:48,315
On a day like today,

452
00:28:48,315 --> 00:28:49,399
just going straight home?

453
00:28:49,399 --> 00:28:50,275
I mean, come on,

454
00:28:50,275 --> 00:28:52,944
how does that even make sense?

455
00:28:52,944 --> 00:28:54,362
Let's throw a party.

456
00:28:54,362 --> 00:28:56,573
Oh, I wish I could,

457
00:28:56,573 --> 00:28:58,783
but I have to get home and see Woo Joo.

458
00:28:58,783 --> 00:29:01,335
Come on, just one drink. Please?

459
00:29:03,330 --> 00:29:05,714
You've barely made time
for me lately, you know that?

460
00:29:07,375 --> 00:29:09,002
You should go.

461
00:29:09,002 --> 00:29:12,304
Wait, you haven't left yet?

462
00:29:14,049 --> 00:29:15,592
Hello.

463
00:29:15,592 --> 00:29:17,552
Right?

464
00:29:17,552 --> 00:29:19,809
We've earned a night out, haven't we?

465
00:29:19,809 --> 00:29:20,777
You know what,

466
00:29:20,777 --> 00:29:23,308
why don't you tag along?

467
00:29:23,308 --> 00:29:24,643
Who, me?

468
00:29:24,643 --> 00:29:26,626
Yeah, come celebrate with us.

469
00:29:26,626 --> 00:29:28,021
Celebrate what exactly?

470
00:29:28,021 --> 00:29:29,189
You don't know yet?

471
00:29:29,189 --> 00:29:31,483
Well, Hyun Jin...

472
00:29:31,483 --> 00:29:33,276
Hyun Jin's

473
00:29:33,276 --> 00:29:35,820
about to be officially brought on full-time.

474
00:29:35,820 --> 00:29:37,864
No way, really?

475
00:29:37,864 --> 00:29:39,157
I'm sorry.

476
00:29:39,157 --> 00:29:41,034
Why didn't you say anything?

477
00:29:41,034 --> 00:29:43,328
You've worked so hard.

478
00:29:43,328 --> 00:29:44,704
Congratulations.

479
00:29:44,704 --> 00:29:46,836
Oh, thanks.

480
00:29:46,836 --> 00:29:49,125
I was going to tell you at home.

481
00:29:49,125 --> 00:29:51,836
Nothing's been officially announced yet anyway.

482
00:29:51,836 --> 00:29:55,006
At home.

483
00:29:55,006 --> 00:29:56,841
Please read the room.

484
00:29:56,841 --> 00:30:00,053
How about a quick beer
at that spot around the corner?

485
00:30:00,053 --> 00:30:02,931
You can't skip the toast on a night like this.

486
00:30:02,931 --> 00:30:05,357
Now there's someone who knows what's up.

487
00:30:06,184 --> 00:30:08,144
Just one drink.

488
00:30:08,144 --> 00:30:10,779
You really can't do just one?

489
00:30:13,608 --> 00:30:15,151
Fine, let's go.

490
00:30:15,151 --> 00:30:15,985
- Let's go.
- Go?

491
00:30:15,985 --> 00:30:17,070
- Yeah.
- Let's go.

492
00:30:17,070 --> 00:30:18,822
Yes! Let's go.

493
00:30:18,822 --> 00:30:20,699
Let's go.

494
00:30:20,699 --> 00:30:22,333
You've been through a lot.

495
00:30:23,159 --> 00:30:24,244
This is good.

496
00:30:24,244 --> 00:30:26,162
How is it, kids? Good?

497
00:30:26,162 --> 00:30:27,497
- It's great!
- So good!

498
00:30:27,497 --> 00:30:29,840
If it's good, let me hear it!

499
00:30:30,625 --> 00:30:34,045
Is it yummy, Woo Joo? With Grandpa?

500
00:30:34,045 --> 00:30:36,715
There's nothing
like grilling pork belly at home.

501
00:30:36,715 --> 00:30:37,757
That's right.

502
00:30:37,757 --> 00:30:39,551
Eating out just isn't the same.

503
00:30:39,551 --> 00:30:41,720
Exactly.

504
00:30:41,720 --> 00:30:44,222
Are they running late?

505
00:30:44,222 --> 00:30:47,976
Yeah, she called a bit ago
and said they'd be late.

506
00:30:47,976 --> 00:30:51,438
Sounds like overtime's been
keeping them slammed.

507
00:30:51,438 --> 00:30:53,280
They'll be here soon.

508
00:30:55,358 --> 00:30:57,826
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

509
00:31:03,575 --> 00:31:05,827
Once more, huge congratulations.

510
00:31:05,827 --> 00:31:07,704
I could not be more proud of you.

511
00:31:07,704 --> 00:31:09,372
Congrats.

512
00:31:09,372 --> 00:31:11,912
Honestly though,
if that company had passed on you,

513
00:31:11,912 --> 00:31:12,751
that's on them.

514
00:31:12,751 --> 00:31:14,919
Hire her or not, hire her or not?

515
00:31:14,919 --> 00:31:16,171
Congratulations.

516
00:31:16,171 --> 00:31:18,506
Oh, thank you.

517
00:31:18,506 --> 00:31:21,092
I feel like I can finally breathe again.

518
00:31:21,092 --> 00:31:24,679
So, who might you be?

519
00:31:24,679 --> 00:31:27,599
I've been by Tae Hyung's side

520
00:31:27,599 --> 00:31:28,725
since his street photography days.

521
00:31:28,725 --> 00:31:30,769
His soulmate, if you will.

522
00:31:30,769 --> 00:31:32,903
I'm Oh Seung Taek.

523
00:31:34,230 --> 00:31:36,191
Hyun Jin and I go all the way
back to high school.

524
00:31:36,191 --> 00:31:38,276
Her soulmate, basically.

525
00:31:38,276 --> 00:31:41,154
I'm Baek Se Yeon.

526
00:31:41,154 --> 00:31:43,330
Oh, nice to meet you.

527
00:31:54,667 --> 00:31:56,044
Whenever

528
00:31:56,044 --> 00:31:59,172
you got the short end of the stick at work,

529
00:31:59,172 --> 00:32:01,299
it drove me up the wall.

530
00:32:01,299 --> 00:32:04,427
I'd bolt upright
in the middle of the night just fuming.

531
00:32:04,427 --> 00:32:07,388
I always assumed people at big corporations

532
00:32:07,388 --> 00:32:08,640
would be polished and put-together

533
00:32:08,640 --> 00:32:10,016
like Manager Park,

534
00:32:10,016 --> 00:32:11,251
but apparently that's not the case?

535
00:32:11,251 --> 00:32:12,621
Seriously though,

536
00:32:12,621 --> 00:32:14,395
Manager Park is something else, isn't he?

537
00:32:14,395 --> 00:32:15,814
He's exactly who I want to be.

538
00:32:15,814 --> 00:32:17,778
Really?

539
00:32:17,778 --> 00:32:18,729
How come?

540
00:32:18,729 --> 00:32:20,614
You're not so bad yourself, you know.

541
00:32:20,614 --> 00:32:22,018
Wait, what?

542
00:32:22,018 --> 00:32:25,198
You can't just throw that at me out of nowhere.

543
00:32:25,198 --> 00:32:27,666
My heart actually skipped a beat.

544
00:32:28,539 --> 00:32:31,210
I thought I was your role model.

545
00:32:32,831 --> 00:32:35,208
Easy there, you're going to end up wasted.

546
00:32:35,208 --> 00:32:37,669
Please, what's one tipsy night going to hurt?

547
00:32:37,669 --> 00:32:38,878
Besides,

548
00:32:38,878 --> 00:32:41,798
I can tell
you still don't really know Hyun Jin.

549
00:32:41,798 --> 00:32:44,050
She absolutely refuses
to get drunk around other people.

550
00:32:44,050 --> 00:32:45,802
In college, she'd accept every single drink

551
00:32:45,802 --> 00:32:47,512
the upperclassmen pushed on her,

552
00:32:47,512 --> 00:32:49,556
get everyone home safe,

553
00:32:49,556 --> 00:32:52,642
and not lose it
until she was behind her own door.

554
00:32:52,642 --> 00:32:53,810
Oh yeah,

555
00:32:53,810 --> 00:32:54,978
that does sound like me.

556
00:32:54,978 --> 00:32:57,021
Sounds like you can really handle your drinks.

557
00:32:57,021 --> 00:32:58,697
Cheers.

558
00:32:59,440 --> 00:33:01,109
That's not really what it is.

559
00:33:01,109 --> 00:33:02,443
When I drink too much, my guard comes down,

560
00:33:02,443 --> 00:33:04,362
and once it's down, I want to lean on someone,

561
00:33:04,362 --> 00:33:05,947
and before I know it, they're seeing

562
00:33:05,947 --> 00:33:07,615
the worst version of me.

563
00:33:07,615 --> 00:33:09,833
I just don't want that.

564
00:33:10,910 --> 00:33:12,829
Oh, and that's just the beginning.

565
00:33:12,829 --> 00:33:15,331
Hyun Jin and I have known each other

566
00:33:15,331 --> 00:33:17,208
for a whole decade.

567
00:33:17,208 --> 00:33:18,710
And not once in all that time

568
00:33:18,710 --> 00:33:20,128
have I ever seen this girl

569
00:33:20,128 --> 00:33:22,797
shed a single tear in front of me.

570
00:33:22,797 --> 00:33:24,716
No. She's actually quite good at both.

571
00:33:24,716 --> 00:33:26,843
That's exactly why I was so shocked

572
00:33:26,843 --> 00:33:29,178
when she told me you guys drank
and slept together.

573
00:33:29,178 --> 00:33:31,264
You slept

574
00:33:31,264 --> 00:33:32,432
together?

575
00:33:32,432 --> 00:33:33,474
Lower your voice.

576
00:33:33,474 --> 00:33:35,018
Are you trying to spread this around?

577
00:33:35,018 --> 00:33:36,185
Let me clarify.

578
00:33:36,185 --> 00:33:38,438
It's not that we slept together.
We were just really drunk.

579
00:33:38,438 --> 00:33:39,772
So we wound up in the same bed.

580
00:33:39,772 --> 00:33:41,107
In the same bed?

581
00:33:41,107 --> 00:33:42,775
Why are you spelling that out?

582
00:33:42,775 --> 00:33:44,485
You're only making it sound worse.

583
00:33:44,485 --> 00:33:45,486
We only slept. That's all.

584
00:33:45,486 --> 00:33:47,697
- We literally just slept.
- Okay.

585
00:33:47,697 --> 00:33:50,082
Did you hold each other...

586
00:33:53,745 --> 00:33:55,096
You okay?

587
00:33:57,081 --> 00:33:59,000
I was stressing over Woo Joo,

588
00:33:59,000 --> 00:34:00,710
so I scarfed down my food,

589
00:34:00,710 --> 00:34:02,503
and now my stomach feels weird.

590
00:34:02,503 --> 00:34:03,922
What kind of weird?

591
00:34:03,922 --> 00:34:06,132
I don't know.

592
00:34:06,132 --> 00:34:08,384
Maybe I have indigestion.

593
00:34:08,384 --> 00:34:10,219
This is driving me crazy.

594
00:34:10,219 --> 00:34:11,895
Let me see your hand.

595
00:34:17,936 --> 00:34:19,354
That hurts.

596
00:34:19,354 --> 00:34:21,481
It hurts, so I need to massage it out.

597
00:34:21,481 --> 00:34:23,149
Just hang in there.

598
00:34:23,149 --> 00:34:25,451
Count to ten for me.

599
00:34:26,699 --> 00:34:29,989
One, two, three, four.

600
00:34:29,989 --> 00:34:31,707
Five.

601
00:34:33,159 --> 00:34:34,835
Six.

602
00:34:38,957 --> 00:34:40,674
Seven.

603
00:34:44,128 --> 00:34:45,888
Eight.

604
00:34:57,396 --> 00:34:58,851
What?

605
00:34:58,851 --> 00:35:00,569
Hello?

606
00:35:03,064 --> 00:35:04,782
What?

607
00:35:06,442 --> 00:35:07,610
Hyun Jin.

608
00:35:07,610 --> 00:35:09,195
Woo Joo!

609
00:35:09,195 --> 00:35:10,871
We have to hurry.

610
00:35:16,160 --> 00:35:17,620
Gosh, what do we do?

611
00:35:17,620 --> 00:35:18,788
Woo Joo, are you alright?

612
00:35:18,788 --> 00:35:19,789
What's going on?

613
00:35:19,789 --> 00:35:21,290
Why did this come out of nowhere?

614
00:35:21,290 --> 00:35:23,209
When did this start?

615
00:35:23,210 --> 00:35:31,210
(Watch on www.kisskh.club Support Admin)

616
00:35:23,209 --> 00:35:25,906
Woo Joo, does it hurt?

617
00:35:25,906 --> 00:35:26,921
What happened?

618
00:35:26,921 --> 00:35:28,756
Look at this, it just showed up.

619
00:35:28,756 --> 00:35:30,133
His skin's breaking out.

620
00:35:30,133 --> 00:35:32,538
Come here.

621
00:35:37,849 --> 00:35:39,517
Did he have any strawberries?

622
00:35:39,517 --> 00:35:40,476
Strawberries...

623
00:35:40,476 --> 00:35:41,686
Did he eat some?

624
00:35:41,686 --> 00:35:43,104
No, he didn't eat any.

625
00:35:43,104 --> 00:35:45,732
He was playing with one earlier,
so I took it away.

626
00:35:45,732 --> 00:35:47,358
Is he allergic to strawberries?

627
00:35:47,358 --> 00:35:49,861
No one ever mentioned that.

628
00:35:49,861 --> 00:35:51,654
It looks like a strawberry allergy.

629
00:35:51,654 --> 00:35:52,739
My oldest child

630
00:35:52,739 --> 00:35:54,073
had the same allergy.

631
00:35:54,073 --> 00:35:56,325
- Gosh.
- What should we do?

632
00:35:56,325 --> 00:35:58,619
At least he didn't swallow any.

633
00:35:58,619 --> 00:36:00,204
I'll rinse him off first.

634
00:36:00,204 --> 00:36:01,581
I'll wash him up,

635
00:36:01,581 --> 00:36:03,332
so please bring an ice pack or a cold towel.

636
00:36:03,332 --> 00:36:04,250
We have ice.

637
00:36:04,250 --> 00:36:06,210
Mom, there's ice right there.

638
00:36:06,210 --> 00:36:08,220
It's over there.

639
00:36:12,467 --> 00:36:14,010
Hey.

640
00:36:14,010 --> 00:36:16,763
- Thank you.
- Oh, you came too?

641
00:36:16,763 --> 00:36:18,852
What happened?

642
00:36:18,852 --> 00:36:19,893
Hyun Jin.

643
00:36:19,893 --> 00:36:22,901
Does he have a strawberry allergy?

644
00:36:23,728 --> 00:36:25,772
I'm not sure.

645
00:36:25,772 --> 00:36:27,940
She hasn't been caring for him long,

646
00:36:27,940 --> 00:36:29,442
so she might not know.

647
00:36:29,442 --> 00:36:30,860
Thankfully,

648
00:36:30,860 --> 00:36:33,196
his grandpa handled it right away,

649
00:36:33,196 --> 00:36:36,032
so he's fine now. Don't panic.

650
00:36:36,032 --> 00:36:38,242
If he hadn't stepped in,
it could've been serious.

651
00:36:38,242 --> 00:36:40,745
Woo Jin was allergic too.

652
00:36:40,745 --> 00:36:42,246
Even touching one

653
00:36:42,246 --> 00:36:43,414
made him itchy and red.

654
00:36:43,414 --> 00:36:45,465
It was itchy.

655
00:36:47,960 --> 00:36:49,545
Woo Joo, let's go.

656
00:36:49,545 --> 00:36:51,221
Let's head out.

657
00:36:58,179 --> 00:37:00,022
I'm sorry.

658
00:37:09,857 --> 00:37:11,526
I've seen him fall asleep,

659
00:37:11,526 --> 00:37:13,111
so I'll get going.

660
00:37:13,111 --> 00:37:15,329
You two should wash up and rest.

661
00:37:16,405 --> 00:37:18,449
Thank you so much.

662
00:37:18,449 --> 00:37:20,326
If it weren't for you,

663
00:37:20,326 --> 00:37:22,411
we could've been in real trouble.

664
00:37:22,411 --> 00:37:24,122
No need to thank me.

665
00:37:24,122 --> 00:37:26,332
If he starts itching tonight,

666
00:37:26,332 --> 00:37:28,209
don't let him scratch too much,

667
00:37:28,209 --> 00:37:31,337
and take him to the hospital if it gets worse.

668
00:37:31,337 --> 00:37:32,503
Okay.

669
00:37:32,503 --> 00:37:33,506
I'm heading out.

670
00:37:33,506 --> 00:37:35,265
Thank you.

671
00:38:23,890 --> 00:38:26,782
You forgot this.

672
00:38:28,352 --> 00:38:30,104
I can be so absentminded.

673
00:38:30,104 --> 00:38:32,231
Sorry you had to come all this way

674
00:38:32,231 --> 00:38:34,233
just for this.

675
00:38:34,233 --> 00:38:37,869
Why do you keep that picture with you?

676
00:38:42,116 --> 00:38:43,875
Oh, this...

677
00:38:45,411 --> 00:38:47,580
No matter how tough things are,

678
00:38:47,580 --> 00:38:51,375
when I see this picture,
it somehow gives me energy.

679
00:38:51,375 --> 00:38:53,836
Where are you living these days?

680
00:38:53,836 --> 00:38:56,263
Oh, me?

681
00:38:57,924 --> 00:39:00,934
The goshiwon right up the road.

682
00:39:02,637 --> 00:39:04,217
A goshiwon?

683
00:39:05,514 --> 00:39:07,767
Goshiwons are really well done nowadays,

684
00:39:07,767 --> 00:39:09,443
just like hotels.

685
00:39:12,605 --> 00:39:16,324
Anyway, I appreciate what you did today.

686
00:39:17,109 --> 00:39:18,778
What?

687
00:39:18,778 --> 00:39:22,414
I said I appreciate it, and last time too,

688
00:39:23,491 --> 00:39:25,243
and today, because of you,

689
00:39:25,243 --> 00:39:27,794
Woo Joo turned out just fine.

690
00:39:35,836 --> 00:39:37,614
Tae Hyung.

691
00:39:38,923 --> 00:39:40,424
Whenever you need me,

692
00:39:40,424 --> 00:39:43,052
just reach out anytime.

693
00:39:43,052 --> 00:39:46,104
That little one Woo Joo
keeps staying on my mind too.

694
00:40:02,905 --> 00:40:04,824
But could you

695
00:40:04,824 --> 00:40:07,542
give me one chance?

696
00:40:20,923 --> 00:40:22,682
Hey.

697
00:40:24,343 --> 00:40:26,304
Why the milk?

698
00:40:26,304 --> 00:40:28,523
You seemed stressed out.

699
00:40:28,523 --> 00:40:30,391
When you can't fall asleep, this really helps.

700
00:40:30,391 --> 00:40:32,268
Go ahead and drink it.

701
00:40:32,268 --> 00:40:33,985
Thanks.

702
00:40:41,235 --> 00:40:42,987
But

703
00:40:42,987 --> 00:40:45,372
I probably won't get any sleep anyway.

704
00:40:46,032 --> 00:40:47,541
Really?

705
00:40:51,287 --> 00:40:53,210
Then how about we do it together?

706
00:40:53,210 --> 00:40:54,248
Do what?

707
00:40:54,248 --> 00:40:56,250
Stay up together.

708
00:40:56,250 --> 00:40:57,793
On nights like this,
lying awake all by yourself,

709
00:40:57,793 --> 00:40:59,803
that's just so lonely.

710
00:41:01,005 --> 00:41:03,507
If we stay up together,

711
00:41:03,507 --> 00:41:04,842
then there's just two exhausted people...

712
00:41:08,012 --> 00:41:09,379
I got F again.

713
00:41:09,379 --> 00:41:11,140
I swear I'm such an F.

714
00:41:11,140 --> 00:41:12,683
I'm really great at connecting with people

715
00:41:12,683 --> 00:41:15,770
and I look after people really well, you know.

716
00:41:15,770 --> 00:41:17,480
Or maybe I don't?

717
00:41:17,480 --> 00:41:19,148
Maybe I'm only nice to my inner circle,

718
00:41:19,148 --> 00:41:21,363
only sweet to my friends?

719
00:41:21,363 --> 00:41:23,201
That can't be it, though. I'm like my sister,

720
00:41:23,201 --> 00:41:24,160
so I've always been the friendly type.

721
00:41:24,160 --> 00:41:25,300
[Pediatrics, Family Medicine]

722
00:41:25,300 --> 00:41:27,476
Open wide and say "Ah".

723
00:41:30,305 --> 00:41:33,250
Fortunately, since the cause was caught early
and dealt with immediately,

724
00:41:33,250 --> 00:41:35,046
there are no other issues.

725
00:41:36,644 --> 00:41:38,855
The allergy test results also indicate

726
00:41:38,855 --> 00:41:39,897
that apart from the strawberry allergy,

727
00:41:39,897 --> 00:41:41,607
there aren't any other allergic reactions,

728
00:41:41,607 --> 00:41:42,734
so there's no need to worry.

729
00:41:42,734 --> 00:41:45,695
Yes, thank you.

730
00:41:45,695 --> 00:41:47,788
Woo Joo, you went through a lot.

731
00:41:51,117 --> 00:41:54,563
Since you were
such a trooper at the doctor today,

732
00:41:54,563 --> 00:41:55,955
I'm getting you a treat,

733
00:41:55,955 --> 00:41:57,714
sound good?

734
00:42:00,293 --> 00:42:01,978
Our Woo Joo.

735
00:42:03,113 --> 00:42:04,575
Did you miss me?

736
00:42:06,799 --> 00:42:09,010
Are you coming back from the hospital?

737
00:42:09,010 --> 00:42:10,470
What's the word? Is he alright?

738
00:42:10,470 --> 00:42:13,181
Yes, because you took
such good care of him yesterday,

739
00:42:13,181 --> 00:42:14,640
they said everything's fine.

740
00:42:14,640 --> 00:42:15,308
Thank goodness.

741
00:42:15,308 --> 00:42:18,561
I appreciate what you did yesterday, again.

742
00:42:18,561 --> 00:42:19,437
This is something

743
00:42:19,437 --> 00:42:21,189
I should've been aware of from the start.

744
00:42:21,189 --> 00:42:22,732
Oh, please.

745
00:42:22,732 --> 00:42:24,650
No one has it all figured out from day one.

746
00:42:24,650 --> 00:42:26,962
You just pick things up as you go.

747
00:42:30,907 --> 00:42:32,575
Tae Hyung also said thanks to me.

748
00:42:32,575 --> 00:42:33,868
Of course a grandpa can't stand

749
00:42:33,868 --> 00:42:35,828
watching his grandson be sick,

750
00:42:35,828 --> 00:42:37,705
so quit thanking me so much.

751
00:42:37,705 --> 00:42:39,082
It's almost hurtful.

752
00:42:39,082 --> 00:42:42,353
He actually said thanks?

753
00:42:44,337 --> 00:42:45,797
It looks like things are

754
00:42:45,797 --> 00:42:48,098
improving a bit from before, right?

755
00:42:48,966 --> 00:42:51,643
Yeah, thankfully.

756
00:42:52,553 --> 00:42:55,848
I know it's late,

757
00:42:55,848 --> 00:42:58,184
but going forward, I truly want to be

758
00:42:58,184 --> 00:43:01,028
a real father to Tae Hyung.

759
00:43:02,522 --> 00:43:04,232
So, about that,

760
00:43:04,232 --> 00:43:06,067
would you mind

761
00:43:06,067 --> 00:43:08,368
helping me out?

762
00:43:09,487 --> 00:43:11,205
Me?

763
00:43:17,662 --> 00:43:19,497
Oh, you're here?

764
00:43:19,497 --> 00:43:21,874
What did the doctor say?

765
00:43:21,874 --> 00:43:23,084
Nothing's wrong,

766
00:43:23,084 --> 00:43:24,836
and he has no allergies
other than the strawberry one.

767
00:43:24,836 --> 00:43:27,471
Oh, good to hear.

768
00:43:31,217 --> 00:43:32,885
Tae Hyung.

769
00:43:32,885 --> 00:43:35,430
Do you have any plans tonight?

770
00:43:35,430 --> 00:43:37,105
Tonight?

771
00:43:38,182 --> 00:43:40,309
Not really anything special, why?

772
00:43:40,309 --> 00:43:42,854
Well, we've been depending so heavily

773
00:43:42,854 --> 00:43:44,814
on your dad recently,

774
00:43:44,814 --> 00:43:48,033
so I was thinking maybe
we could treat him to a meal.

775
00:43:49,360 --> 00:43:52,537
Woo Joo is really fond of his grandpa too.

776
00:44:04,000 --> 00:44:07,378
But there's no pressure or anything.

777
00:44:07,378 --> 00:44:08,754
If you'd really rather not,

778
00:44:08,754 --> 00:44:11,640
it can just be the three of us for dinner.

779
00:44:13,759 --> 00:44:16,345
Let's eat with him, too.

780
00:44:16,345 --> 00:44:17,388
Really?

781
00:44:17,388 --> 00:44:19,064
For real?

782
00:44:20,766 --> 00:44:23,811
I mean, it's just dinner.
Don't make a big deal out of it.

783
00:44:23,811 --> 00:44:26,571
And where are you going
to take Woo Joo, anyway?

784
00:44:30,610 --> 00:44:32,653
Stop.

785
00:44:32,653 --> 00:44:34,506
Police car.

786
00:44:40,912 --> 00:44:42,921
What are you doing standing out here?

787
00:44:46,667 --> 00:44:51,005
They invited me over for dinner.

788
00:44:51,005 --> 00:44:53,098
Okay.

789
00:44:54,270 --> 00:44:56,636
Then why aren't you going in?
Just standing here like that.

790
00:44:56,636 --> 00:44:58,520
Looking all suspicious.

791
00:44:59,347 --> 00:45:03,752
No, it's just...
now that I'm actually about to go in,

792
00:45:03,752 --> 00:45:05,339
I feel a little... you know.

793
00:45:20,910 --> 00:45:22,870
Oh, you scared me.

794
00:45:22,870 --> 00:45:24,671
Hello.

795
00:45:26,207 --> 00:45:27,750
Hi.

796
00:45:27,750 --> 00:45:30,260
Please, come in.

797
00:45:34,257 --> 00:45:35,299
Yeah,

798
00:45:35,299 --> 00:45:37,309
take care.

799
00:45:41,581 --> 00:45:45,017
You really went all out. You shouldn't have.

800
00:45:45,017 --> 00:45:46,519
I just whipped it up in no time.

801
00:45:46,519 --> 00:45:48,396
Help yourself.

802
00:45:48,396 --> 00:45:51,156
Well, don't mind if I do.

803
00:45:57,572 --> 00:46:00,533
They told me you work at a food company,

804
00:46:00,533 --> 00:46:03,244
and you can really cook.

805
00:46:03,244 --> 00:46:05,955
I hope it suits your taste.

806
00:46:05,955 --> 00:46:08,006
This is amazing.

807
00:46:12,211 --> 00:46:14,297
Tae Hyung, have a bite.

808
00:46:14,297 --> 00:46:16,181
It's so good.

809
00:46:24,932 --> 00:46:26,350
Have some rice too.

810
00:46:26,350 --> 00:46:30,438
There you go, look at you eating so well.

811
00:46:30,438 --> 00:46:33,858
You eat so well.

812
00:46:33,858 --> 00:46:35,700
I eat so well.

813
00:46:40,740 --> 00:46:43,075
I will feed you. Open wide!

814
00:46:43,075 --> 00:46:45,127
You eat so well.

815
00:46:45,995 --> 00:46:49,339
Woo Joo seems to really adore you.

816
00:46:49,999 --> 00:46:52,835
He seems to know I'm family,
even though he's so little.

817
00:46:52,835 --> 00:46:54,511
Right?

818
00:46:59,884 --> 00:47:01,844
Oh, right. I need to change his diaper.

819
00:47:01,844 --> 00:47:02,678
Let me handle it.

820
00:47:02,678 --> 00:47:04,597
No, I've got it.

821
00:47:04,597 --> 00:47:06,098
You just sit back.

822
00:47:06,098 --> 00:47:08,436
Come on, Woo Joo, diaper time.

823
00:47:10,519 --> 00:47:12,237
Let's go.

824
00:47:17,860 --> 00:47:19,494
Alright.

825
00:47:31,499 --> 00:47:33,216
There's something...

826
00:47:35,086 --> 00:47:38,680
I've always wanted to know.

827
00:47:40,049 --> 00:47:41,933
Back then...

828
00:47:42,802 --> 00:47:45,346
why did you leave me behind?

829
00:47:45,346 --> 00:47:47,348
What?

830
00:47:47,348 --> 00:47:49,308
I mean, it's just...

831
00:47:49,308 --> 00:47:51,443
I honestly want to know.

832
00:47:52,728 --> 00:47:54,855
Nobody ever told me the reason,

833
00:47:54,855 --> 00:47:57,782
and it's eaten at me my entire life.

834
00:48:02,279 --> 00:48:04,664
Honestly, I wanted to

835
00:48:05,491 --> 00:48:07,542
reach out to you too.

836
00:48:09,328 --> 00:48:12,373
You can't imagine
how badly I wanted to see you.

837
00:48:12,373 --> 00:48:16,635
But when I finally snapped out of it
and made it back home,

838
00:48:17,670 --> 00:48:19,596
you were already gone.

839
00:48:22,174 --> 00:48:23,592
According to Woo Jin,

840
00:48:23,592 --> 00:48:27,388
you wanted nothing to do with a useless dad.

841
00:48:27,388 --> 00:48:29,181
That's why I never reached out.

842
00:48:29,181 --> 00:48:31,566
No, I chose not to.

843
00:48:32,351 --> 00:48:34,444
Forget about helping,

844
00:48:35,438 --> 00:48:38,240
I refused to be a dad who only drags you down.

845
00:48:39,525 --> 00:48:40,818
Hold on, Woo Jin said that?

846
00:48:40,818 --> 00:48:42,827
He said I said that?

847
00:48:43,571 --> 00:48:45,539
Woo Jin told me

848
00:48:47,032 --> 00:48:51,086
he was tired of a family
that only weighs each other down.

849
00:48:52,830 --> 00:48:55,382
He wanted to pretend
we never existed to each other.

850
00:48:56,375 --> 00:48:58,627
He said once he dropped everything,

851
00:48:58,627 --> 00:49:00,804
he felt so free.

852
00:49:03,716 --> 00:49:06,969
And honestly, he had a point.

853
00:49:06,969 --> 00:49:08,895
You already know.

854
00:49:10,222 --> 00:49:12,933
Wasn't I drowning in debt?

855
00:49:12,933 --> 00:49:14,859
If I had shown up,

856
00:49:15,728 --> 00:49:18,697
you would've gotten dragged into my problems.

857
00:49:22,777 --> 00:49:26,489
So is it all paid off now?

858
00:49:26,489 --> 00:49:29,074
Oh, absolutely.

859
00:49:29,074 --> 00:49:31,585
I never could've shown up here otherwise.

860
00:49:35,456 --> 00:49:38,167
I'm sorry.
Your dad shouldn't have been this pathetic.

861
00:49:38,167 --> 00:49:40,711
Please, enough with the apologies already.

862
00:49:40,711 --> 00:49:43,221
That's seriously all you've got?

863
00:49:44,131 --> 00:49:46,182
It's just that I feel so bad.

864
00:49:46,967 --> 00:49:49,094
If it were up to me,

865
00:49:49,094 --> 00:49:51,680
I'd see your face every single day

866
00:49:51,680 --> 00:49:54,316
and give you everything I couldn't before...

867
00:49:57,478 --> 00:50:00,439
You can leave Woo Joo with me anytime.

868
00:50:00,439 --> 00:50:02,399
We're family, after all.

869
00:50:02,399 --> 00:50:05,660
That beats leaving him
with some stranger, doesn't it?

870
00:50:25,589 --> 00:50:27,932
It's 2435.

871
00:50:30,537 --> 00:50:32,263
What?

872
00:50:32,263 --> 00:50:35,315
You'll need the door code, won't you?

873
00:50:36,392 --> 00:50:40,153
If you're watching Woo Joo anytime.

874
00:50:44,608 --> 00:50:46,193
Yeah.

875
00:50:46,193 --> 00:50:48,411
Absolutely.

876
00:50:49,113 --> 00:50:51,247
Whenever you need me, just call.

877
00:51:25,441 --> 00:51:27,610
He wanted to pretend

878
00:51:27,610 --> 00:51:30,029
we never existed to each other.

879
00:51:30,029 --> 00:51:31,989
He said once he dropped everything,

880
00:51:31,989 --> 00:51:34,290
he felt so free.

881
00:51:37,411 --> 00:51:38,579
So,

882
00:51:38,579 --> 00:51:40,497
you're seriously never making up with her?

883
00:51:40,497 --> 00:51:42,750
She worries about you so much.

884
00:51:42,750 --> 00:51:44,126
Just come home already.

885
00:51:44,126 --> 00:51:45,711
I don't want to.

886
00:51:45,711 --> 00:51:48,297
Be real, you're uncomfortable with me around.

887
00:51:48,297 --> 00:51:51,057
That's not true at all.

888
00:51:52,676 --> 00:51:54,419
Hyun Jin.

889
00:51:54,419 --> 00:51:55,554
Do you know why I wasn't upset at all,

890
00:51:55,554 --> 00:51:57,848
even though Hyun Joo rejected me

891
00:51:57,848 --> 00:52:00,150
every single time I proposed?

892
00:52:01,477 --> 00:52:02,895
What is it?

893
00:52:02,895 --> 00:52:05,155
Because I would've done the exact same thing.

894
00:52:05,773 --> 00:52:07,733
If I were in her shoes,

895
00:52:07,733 --> 00:52:10,235
my little sister would always come first.

896
00:52:10,235 --> 00:52:12,529
That's a given.

897
00:52:12,529 --> 00:52:13,948
So

898
00:52:13,948 --> 00:52:16,033
this time, you need to be the one

899
00:52:16,033 --> 00:52:18,202
to say sorry to your sister first.

900
00:52:18,202 --> 00:52:22,331
You told her that you're nothing
but a burden to her, didn't you?

901
00:52:22,331 --> 00:52:26,217
Seriously, you don't say that to family.

902
00:52:44,311 --> 00:52:46,397
Oh my, it's been so long.

903
00:52:46,397 --> 00:52:47,481
Here, have some ice cream.

904
00:52:47,481 --> 00:52:48,691
That's okay.

905
00:52:48,691 --> 00:52:50,234
- You're on the clock, right?
- Yes.

906
00:52:50,234 --> 00:52:52,027
By the way, the burglar

907
00:52:52,027 --> 00:52:53,487
who hit our villa last time,

908
00:52:53,487 --> 00:52:54,571
what ever happened to him?

909
00:52:54,571 --> 00:52:57,475
He cleaned out every single unit on the block,

910
00:52:57,475 --> 00:52:58,701
it was pure madness.

911
00:52:58,701 --> 00:53:01,120
It still makes me furious
just thinking about that little rat.

912
00:53:01,120 --> 00:53:03,998
His case already went to the prosecutor.

913
00:53:03,998 --> 00:53:04,707
Is that so?

914
00:53:04,707 --> 00:53:05,708
We checked out his place

915
00:53:05,708 --> 00:53:08,069
and he'd been hoarding
all kinds of stolen goods.

916
00:53:08,069 --> 00:53:09,878
But here's the odd part,

917
00:53:09,878 --> 00:53:12,131
he flat-out refused to admit
he ever touched Unit 206 at Yooseong Villa,

918
00:53:12,131 --> 00:53:13,465
denied it till the very end.

919
00:53:13,465 --> 00:53:15,217
That doesn't add up.

920
00:53:15,217 --> 00:53:16,635
They said the door was even left unlocked.

921
00:53:16,635 --> 00:53:17,720
Exactly, that's my point.

922
00:53:17,720 --> 00:53:18,762
Even with clear evidence,

923
00:53:18,762 --> 00:53:21,557
he kept insisting he never touched 206.

924
00:53:21,557 --> 00:53:24,184
He confessed to planning
the break-in at Unit 206,

925
00:53:24,184 --> 00:53:26,603
but insisted he never went through with it.

926
00:53:26,603 --> 00:53:28,689
He says it wasn't 206?

927
00:53:28,689 --> 00:53:31,066
They just said my testimony helped.

928
00:53:31,066 --> 00:53:34,862
I kept noticing someone
hovering around that door,

929
00:53:34,862 --> 00:53:36,822
and it struck me as shady,

930
00:53:36,822 --> 00:53:39,207
so I memorized what he looked like.

931
00:53:41,102 --> 00:53:42,661
I'll see you around.

932
00:53:42,661 --> 00:53:44,546
Right, take care.

933
00:53:47,108 --> 00:53:50,077
[Goun Life Insurance]

934
00:53:57,744 --> 00:54:00,512
Here's your reissued insurance certificate.

935
00:54:00,512 --> 00:54:03,223
Would you mind looking it over?

936
00:54:03,223 --> 00:54:04,899
Sure.

937
00:54:07,905 --> 00:54:10,272
[Insured, Woo Hyun Joo]

938
00:54:10,272 --> 00:54:13,108
I definitely saw
my sister had gathered up the paperwork,

939
00:54:13,108 --> 00:54:15,660
but I couldn't track it down anywhere.

940
00:54:16,314 --> 00:54:18,890
So every document that's needed
has been turned in now, correct?

941
00:54:18,890 --> 00:54:19,907
Yes.

942
00:54:19,907 --> 00:54:22,201
Just have your personal seal
ready ahead of time,

943
00:54:22,201 --> 00:54:23,702
and once I wrap up the remaining steps,

944
00:54:23,702 --> 00:54:25,454
I'll reach out to you shortly.

945
00:54:25,454 --> 00:54:27,456
Oh, were you able to walk

946
00:54:27,456 --> 00:54:29,583
the other guardian through everything?

947
00:54:29,583 --> 00:54:33,303
They seemed to have
a lot of questions since last time.

948
00:54:33,921 --> 00:54:36,055
The other guardian?

949
00:54:39,968 --> 00:54:42,346
I brought this up before,

950
00:54:42,346 --> 00:54:43,764
but that guardian

951
00:54:43,764 --> 00:54:46,058
kept reaching out by phone

952
00:54:46,058 --> 00:54:48,143
about the payout procedures and who qualifies,

953
00:54:48,143 --> 00:54:51,313
so we ended up visiting them in person.

954
00:54:51,313 --> 00:54:53,148
They never gave a name,

955
00:54:53,148 --> 00:54:55,234
only introduced themselves as a guardian.

956
00:54:55,234 --> 00:54:59,363
A man, looked about middle-aged.

957
00:54:59,363 --> 00:55:00,989
Hey, Woo Hyun Jin,

958
00:55:00,989 --> 00:55:03,082
what's on your mind?

959
00:55:15,196 --> 00:55:16,213
Hyun Jin.

960
00:55:16,213 --> 00:55:18,632
Oh, hello.

961
00:55:18,632 --> 00:55:20,676
How did you end up picking up Woo Joo?

962
00:55:20,676 --> 00:55:22,469
The lady next door's back was acting up,

963
00:55:22,469 --> 00:55:24,687
so I picked Woo Joo up from daycare instead.

964
00:55:25,681 --> 00:55:27,808
Oh, I appreciate that.

965
00:55:27,808 --> 00:55:30,394
Oh, it was nothing.

966
00:55:30,394 --> 00:55:34,314
Could I maybe get a glass of water?

967
00:55:34,314 --> 00:55:35,899
Oh, yes, of course.

968
00:55:35,899 --> 00:55:37,617
Come on in.

969
00:55:43,824 --> 00:55:46,910
Why are you looking at that room?

970
00:55:46,910 --> 00:55:49,329
Nobody uses this room?

971
00:55:49,329 --> 00:55:52,207
No, not really.

972
00:55:52,207 --> 00:55:54,251
Only introduced themselves as a guardian.

973
00:55:54,251 --> 00:55:57,971
A man, looked about middle-aged.

974
00:55:58,922 --> 00:56:02,016
Do you happen to...

975
00:56:07,806 --> 00:56:09,959
I'm back.

976
00:56:09,959 --> 00:56:13,437
Oh, you just got off work?

977
00:56:13,437 --> 00:56:15,613
Yeah.

978
00:56:17,441 --> 00:56:19,193
Hyun Jin,

979
00:56:19,193 --> 00:56:21,202
what were you going to say?

980
00:56:26,267 --> 00:56:29,023
Here's your water.

981
00:56:35,318 --> 00:56:38,003
[Amwol Goshiwon]

982
00:56:38,003 --> 00:56:40,214
Oh, come on,

983
00:56:40,214 --> 00:56:42,841
just hold on a little longer.

984
00:56:42,841 --> 00:56:44,976
I mean it this time.

985
00:56:49,932 --> 00:56:51,858
Darn it.

986
00:56:53,878 --> 00:56:56,717
I've got a solid lead on the money.

987
00:56:57,314 --> 00:56:59,574
Yeah, that thing I brought up before.

988
00:57:00,359 --> 00:57:03,745
Look, quit pressuring me and just be patient.

989
00:57:06,978 --> 00:57:08,976
The bus leaves in 15 minutes.
We need to head out.

990
00:57:08,976 --> 00:57:10,285
Alright, let's go.

991
00:57:10,285 --> 00:57:12,211
Oh, wait a sec.

992
00:57:19,336 --> 00:57:20,462
It's here. Let's get on.

993
00:57:21,964 --> 00:57:23,382
Oh right, the stove!

994
00:57:23,382 --> 00:57:25,342
I don't think I turned off the stove.

995
00:57:25,342 --> 00:57:26,885
Didn't you turn it off earlier?

996
00:57:26,885 --> 00:57:29,554
I can't remember...

997
00:57:29,554 --> 00:57:32,057
You go ahead. I'll turn it off and catch up.

998
00:57:32,057 --> 00:57:33,684
Hyun Jin.

999
00:57:33,684 --> 00:57:35,852
Hey.

1000
00:57:35,852 --> 00:57:37,779
You're not getting on?

1001
00:58:26,929 --> 00:58:29,519
Where the heck is it?

1002
00:58:49,634 --> 00:58:51,811
Oh, found it.

1003
00:58:59,102 --> 00:59:01,154
Where is my mind?

1004
00:59:06,401 --> 00:59:09,203
Thank goodness, it was already off.

1005
00:59:17,329 --> 00:59:19,088
What's that noise?

1006
00:59:19,873 --> 00:59:21,299
What?

1007
01:00:37,101 --> 01:00:38,144
Are you out of your mind?

1008
01:00:38,144 --> 01:00:39,489
How many times does this make now,

1009
01:00:39,489 --> 01:00:41,280
you putting Hyun Jin in harm's way?

1010
01:00:41,280 --> 01:00:42,864
But we're family.

1011
01:00:42,864 --> 01:00:45,364
Family? What is that even
supposed to mean to us?

1012
01:00:45,364 --> 01:00:48,112
You know what, you're a natural with kids.

1013
01:00:48,112 --> 01:00:51,866
I can be someone
you and Woo Joo always count on.

1014
01:00:51,866 --> 01:00:53,864
Just look at the way those two act together.

1015
01:00:53,864 --> 01:00:55,619
They're definitely a couple, trust me.

1016
01:00:55,619 --> 01:00:57,997
Sun Tae Hyung, could we talk for a moment?

1017
01:00:57,997 --> 01:00:59,832
You can't just walk off like that...

1018
01:00:59,832 --> 01:01:01,375
But honestly, are you okay with this?

1019
01:01:01,375 --> 01:01:03,718
You have feelings for her, don't you?
